   <pb facs="6"/>
   <head>A SONNET so the Christian Reader.</head>
   <l>AChilles neuer durst at once</l>
   <l>With monsters two to fight,</l>
   <l>And yet at once this booke shows thee</l>
   <l>How three to put to flight.</l>
   <l>The Deuil, the World, the Fleshe; and more,</l>
   <l>To conquere Death and sinne;</l>
   <l>And howe to liue, and howe to dye,</l>
   <l>And howe the heauens to winne.</l>
   <l>It is a path to Paradise,</l>
   <l>A port to heauenly blisse,</l>
   <l>It treats of truce, and bringes the peace,</l>
   <l>That euer during is.</l>
   <l>Then reade, and reape the fruites therof.</l>
   <l>And thanke thou for thy gaines</l>
   <l>The God aboue, who raisd vp those,</l>
   <l>That tooke for thee the paines.</l>
   <q>
      <l>Conuertantur qui oderunt Sion.</l>
   </q>
